1
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:55,180


2
00:01:20,057 --> 00:01:21,717
What's with you?

3
00:01:23,737 --> 00:01:28,987
Why are you staring at my face like that?

4
00:01:31,057 --> 00:01:35,277
Hey, why did you hit me? What's wrong with you?

5
00:01:36,197 --> 00:01:37,847
A mosquito. Mosquito, a mosquito.

6
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:40,077
A mosquito tried to suck your blood.

7
00:01:40,077 --> 00:01:42,617
So... I was trying to catch it for you.

8
00:01:42,617 --> 00:01:45,557
A mosquito? What mosquito?

9
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:48,037
There. There, there, there.

10
00:01:48,037 --> 00:01:49,957
- Where? 
 - Wow.

11
00:01:49,957 --> 00:01:52,007
Wow, the weather's so nice.

12
00:01:52,007 --> 00:01:53,217
Oppa, look at the sky.

13
00:01:53,217 --> 00:01:55,557
It's not raining today. It's totally different than yesterday.

14
00:01:55,557 --> 00:01:57,727
Wow, the wind is so fresh.

15
00:01:57,727 --> 00:02:00,367
I need to go out now.

16
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:02,597
Where's the mosquito?

17
00:02:02,597 --> 00:02:04,497
Are there mosquitos here already?

18
00:02:04,497 --> 00:02:06,157
Geez, it hurts.

19
00:02:06,157 --> 00:02:09,017
Why did she hit me so hard?

20
00:02:12,137 --> 00:02:13,537
What?

21
00:02:13,537 --> 00:02:16,977
Do Ra! Do Ra!

22
00:02:16,977 --> 00:02:18,807
What's going on, Do Ra? What is it? 
    

23
00:02:18,807 --> 00:02:20,247
Oppa, look over there.

24
00:02:20,247 --> 00:02:22,987
There's a rainbow. There's a rainbow up there!

25
00:02:23,987 --> 00:02:26,997
Wow, you're right.

26
00:02:26,997 --> 00:02:30,717
Red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and purple.

27
00:02:30,717 --> 00:02:33,057
I've never seen such a vibrant rainbow.

28
00:02:33,057 --> 00:02:35,757
Isn't this so amazing, Oppa?

29
00:02:35,757 --> 00:02:38,137
Oppa, what does this mean?

30
00:02:38,137 --> 00:02:41,767
I think our drama is going to be a hit!

31
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:45,707
I thought something serious happened because you were screaming loudly.

32
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:49,657
Wow, I'm seeing a rainbow today, too.

33
00:02:49,657 --> 00:02:52,647
This really feels like a totally different world.

34
00:02:52,647 --> 00:02:55,767
I love this place. I love it so much.

35
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:58,997
Hey, there are no restaurants, coffee shops,

36
00:02:58,997 --> 00:03:00,587
and not a single person here. But you like it?

37
00:03:00,587 --> 00:03:03,677
Yes, that's why I like it.

38
00:03:03,677 --> 00:03:05,667
You probably don't know how I feel.

39
00:03:05,667 --> 00:03:08,907
I've been like a monkey in a zoo.

40
00:03:08,907 --> 00:03:12,467
Just walking around makes people stare and talk.

41
00:03:12,467 --> 00:03:16,007
People take pictures of me eating, yawning, or dozing off while

42
00:03:16,007 --> 00:03:18,547
waiting on set without consent.

43
00:03:18,547 --> 00:03:20,897
And they say I don't look good in person,

44
00:03:20,897 --> 00:03:25,257
I got plastic surgery or some treatment and whatnot. They talk so much.

45
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:29,967
They call me mean and rude if I avoid them because I'm tired.

46
00:03:32,357 --> 00:03:36,097
But here, no one looks at me,

47
00:03:36,097 --> 00:03:38,917
or takes pictures of me.

48
00:03:41,477 --> 00:03:43,717
It's perfect freedom.

49
00:03:45,377 --> 00:03:47,577
It's been so long.

50
00:03:51,037 --> 00:03:52,887
I'm free.

51
00:03:56,567 --> 00:03:58,737
I feel alive.

52
00:04:04,597 --> 00:04:08,877
By the way, how much do you think an island like this costs?

53
00:04:08,877 --> 00:04:10,537
Why do you ask?

54
00:04:10,537 --> 00:04:12,557
Maybe I'll buy this island,

55
00:04:12,557 --> 00:04:16,717
build a cabin and live here after I retire.

56
00:04:16,717 --> 00:04:18,837
You'll have to make a lot of money, then.

57
00:04:18,837 --> 00:04:21,777
Right? I should work even harder,

58
00:04:21,777 --> 00:04:24,347
make even more money, buy this island,

59
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,947
and turn this into the Do Ra World.

60
00:04:26,947 --> 00:04:29,457
I can just wear a bikini and go to the beach there,

61
00:04:29,457 --> 00:04:31,927
no one would be looking at me.

62
00:04:31,927 --> 00:04:33,387
You're so excited.

63
00:04:33,387 --> 00:04:36,127
I love it just thinking about it.

64
00:04:39,587 --> 00:04:42,777
By the way, if you want to come,

65
00:04:44,597 --> 00:04:46,497
you can.

66
00:04:46,497 --> 00:04:50,187
No, thank you. You beat me, trying to catch a mosquito.

67
00:04:50,187 --> 00:04:52,837
Who knows what would happen if I came here?

68
00:04:54,937 --> 00:04:57,387
Huh? It's a boat!

69
00:04:57,387 --> 00:05:00,547
A boat is coming! We made it!

70
00:05:00,547 --> 00:05:03,307
Excuse me! Over here!

71
00:05:03,307 --> 00:05:04,747
Over here! Over here!

72
00:05:04,747 --> 00:05:09,037
What? Why did the boat come so early?

73
00:05:09,037 --> 00:05:11,637
They could've come much later.

74
00:05:16,097 --> 00:05:18,657
 The bride next to Chairman Gong was 

75
00:05:18,657 --> 00:05:23,597
 that girlfriend who got pregnant and was supposed to marry the student. 

76
00:05:23,597 --> 00:05:25,857
 W-What did you say? 

77
00:05:25,857 --> 00:05:27,127
 That... 

78
00:05:27,127 --> 00:05:29,797
 That was my niece-in-law? 

79
00:05:29,797 --> 00:05:33,187
 Y-You mean Ma Ri's mom? 

80
00:05:37,287 --> 00:05:40,537
She fooled us completely after all that.

81
00:05:40,537 --> 00:05:43,387
She should've behaved herself, then.

82
00:05:43,387 --> 00:05:47,307
She couldn't even manage a child and ruined our family.

83
00:05:47,307 --> 00:05:50,147
Aigoo, that bitch.

84
00:05:50,147 --> 00:05:52,477
What a cunning bitch.

85
00:05:54,347 --> 00:05:58,837
What am I supposed to do? What am I supposed to do?

86
00:06:04,417 --> 00:06:06,577
Auntie, I'm here.

87
00:06:10,127 --> 00:06:15,417
Auntie, I made abalone porridge, your favorite.

88
00:06:15,417 --> 00:06:18,147
I think it turned out pretty tasty.

89
00:06:18,887 --> 00:06:20,997
Here.

90
00:06:20,997 --> 00:06:24,357
Eat this and feel better.

91
00:06:25,917 --> 00:06:28,887
I'm sick because of you right now. How dare you make me this?

92
00:06:28,887 --> 00:06:31,207
A-Auntie.

93
00:06:31,207 --> 00:06:35,397
I can't eat your porridge because I find it disgusting.

94
00:06:35,397 --> 00:06:36,997
How shameless!

95
00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:38,827
You have no shame.

96
00:06:38,827 --> 00:06:39,987
Disgusting?

97
00:06:39,987 --> 00:06:42,647
Auntie, why are you doing this to her now?

98
00:06:42,647 --> 00:06:46,767
Let it out on me if you want to. Don't do this to her.

99
00:06:48,707 --> 00:06:50,977
Honey. Honey!

100
00:06:50,977 --> 00:06:53,147
Who do you think you are?  You have no shame!

101
00:06:53,147 --> 00:06:54,207


102
00:06:54,207 --> 00:06:56,927
Honey, hold on a moment.

103
00:06:58,697 --> 00:07:00,687
I apologize on her behalf.

104
00:07:00,687 --> 00:07:03,117
I'm sorry, Honey.

105
00:07:03,117 --> 00:07:07,477
I can no longer put up with this.

106
00:07:07,477 --> 00:07:10,747
I tried to make her feel better somehow,

107
00:07:10,747 --> 00:07:13,267
- but I don't think I can anymore. 
 - Calm down, Honey.

108
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:17,387
I'll talk to her so she doesn't do this again.

109
00:07:17,387 --> 00:07:21,107
She's just shocked because Ma Ri lashed out at her the other day.

110
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:25,387
I think she's irritable since she's also not in good health.

111
00:07:25,387 --> 00:07:29,547
I know it isn't easy, but please try to understand just once.

112
00:07:29,547 --> 00:07:32,057
What do you mean to understand just once?

113
00:07:32,057 --> 00:07:35,447
How can you say that after seeing what she did to me?

114
00:07:35,447 --> 00:07:37,837
What can we do, then?

115
00:07:37,837 --> 00:07:41,447
I can't understand you acting like this anymore.

116
00:07:43,887 --> 00:07:45,727
Fine.

117
00:07:45,727 --> 00:07:48,387
I'll leave with Ma Ri, then.

118
00:07:48,387 --> 00:07:51,787
You should meet someone new, as Auntie said.

119
00:07:51,787 --> 00:07:55,357
Either have a baby or get a surrogate mother. Do whatever you want.

120
00:07:55,357 --> 00:07:59,047
Honey, how could you say such a thing?

121
00:07:59,047 --> 00:08:02,597
What am I supposed to do if you act like this, too?

122
00:08:36,537 --> 00:08:41,137
What wrong could she have done for you to cause a scene like this?

123
00:08:44,087 --> 00:08:49,437
I wanted to live a long time with you, Auntie.

124
00:08:51,297 --> 00:08:55,647
You should go back to the US now.

125
00:08:56,887 --> 00:09:02,137
Instead, I'll visit you there often.

126
00:09:02,137 --> 00:09:04,667
- Jin Taek. 
 - Let's do that.

127
00:09:04,667 --> 00:09:07,757
Because you keep doing this,

128
00:09:07,757 --> 00:09:11,197
- I have no choice, either. 
 - Jin Taek.

129
00:09:11,197 --> 00:09:14,257
I need to tell you something.

130
00:09:16,247 --> 00:09:18,007
Okay, go ahead.

131
00:09:18,007 --> 00:09:21,777
It's about your wife, Ma Ri's mom.

132
00:09:23,337 --> 00:09:27,477
 No, he wants me to go back just because I threw porridge. 

133
00:09:27,477 --> 00:09:31,517
 He'd refuse to see me again if I bring it up without evidence. 

134
00:09:31,517 --> 00:09:34,747
 He'd never see me again once he turned his back against me. 

135
00:09:34,747 --> 00:09:36,487
What about Soo Yeon?

136
00:09:36,487 --> 00:09:39,647
What are you trying to say now?

137
00:09:40,987 --> 00:09:42,727
Never mind.

138
00:09:44,037 --> 00:09:50,627
I think I overreacted since I worry too much because of my old age.

139
00:09:50,627 --> 00:09:56,357
I gave you two a hard time by only caring about our family.

140
00:09:57,527 --> 00:09:58,977
Auntie.

141
00:09:58,977 --> 00:10:01,257
I'm sorry, Jin Taek.

142
00:10:01,257 --> 00:10:03,167
I'll never do that again.

143
00:10:03,167 --> 00:10:07,127
I'll apologize to Soo Yeon that I was out of line.

144
00:10:13,147 --> 00:10:16,087
You should've been like this sooner.

145
00:10:17,037 --> 00:10:19,057
You know I think of you...

146
00:10:19,957 --> 00:10:23,317
as my mother, right?

147
00:10:23,317 --> 00:10:25,947
Of course, I do.

148
00:10:25,947 --> 00:10:29,317
I won't give you a hard time from now on.

149
00:10:29,317 --> 00:10:31,687
So, go back to work.

150
00:10:33,117 --> 00:10:35,827
Would you be okay on your own?

151
00:10:35,827 --> 00:10:40,187
Don't be silly. What am I, a child?

152
00:10:40,187 --> 00:10:42,957
Don't worry, and get to work.

153
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:49,517
Okay, I will.

154
00:11:02,637 --> 00:11:06,387
Hey, Ms. Jo. Where are you right now?

155
00:11:06,387 --> 00:11:08,647
I'm in Jeju right now.

156
00:11:08,647 --> 00:11:11,247
I came with my family for a vacation.

157
00:11:11,247 --> 00:11:13,007
 Is that so? 

158
00:11:13,007 --> 00:11:15,187
When are you coming back to Seoul?

159
00:11:15,187 --> 00:11:16,857
 We're going back the day after tomorrow. 

160
00:11:16,857 --> 00:11:20,017
 What is it, by the way, Ms. Gong? 

161
00:11:20,017 --> 00:11:23,117
Ms. Jo, I have a favor to ask.

162
00:11:23,117 --> 00:11:29,487
You can tell Chairman Gong what you told me last time, right?

163
00:11:30,387 --> 00:11:33,037
Me? That's a bit...

164
00:11:33,037 --> 00:11:35,697
 Think from my perspective. 

165
00:11:35,697 --> 00:11:38,777
Would you just ignore it if it were about your son?

166
00:11:38,777 --> 00:11:40,567
 That's true, but... 

167
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:43,997
He'll believe you because you saw it yourself.

168
00:11:43,997 --> 00:11:49,057
So, meet Chairman Gong with me and tell him.

169
00:11:49,057 --> 00:11:50,567
I'm begging you.

170
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:52,427
 I'm not sure if that'd be okay. 

171
00:11:52,427 --> 00:11:55,047
I'll be responsible, okay?

172
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:58,427
I won't put you in a difficult position. Don't worry.

173
00:11:58,427 --> 00:12:01,877
 Okay, I'll call you when I return. 

174
00:12:01,877 --> 00:12:04,587
Okay, thank you, Ms. Jo.

175
00:12:04,587 --> 00:12:08,577
Call me as soon as you get back to Seoul, okay?

176
00:12:11,817 --> 00:12:19,587
Yes, it'd be better if he heard it from her and found evidence himself.

177
00:12:19,587 --> 00:12:22,267
That way, he'll realize what's going on.

178
00:12:23,457 --> 00:12:28,107
Mom, it feels so peaceful and nice without Great Aunt.

179
00:12:28,107 --> 00:12:32,167
I hope she just goes back to the US.

180
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:34,687
- Ma Ri. 
 - What?

181
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:38,567
We've been a mess since she came here.

182
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:41,477
You're always frowning, too.

183
00:12:41,477 --> 00:12:46,607
Your face got really ugly because of her.

184
00:12:46,607 --> 00:12:50,757
So, let's tell her to go back to the US.

185
00:12:50,757 --> 00:12:53,647
Ma Ri, you can't say stuff like that.

186
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:57,107
Why not? Do I have to forgive her because she's an elder?

187
00:12:57,107 --> 00:13:01,807
I... I think that's unreasonable.

188
00:13:01,807 --> 00:13:04,757
 Auntie, when did you get back? 

189
00:13:04,757 --> 00:13:07,007
I'm coming back just now.

190
00:13:08,947 --> 00:13:12,827
I would've picked you up if I knew you were coming home today.

191
00:13:12,827 --> 00:13:14,637
Why would you do that?

192
00:13:14,637 --> 00:13:17,957
I was just getting an IV treatment and rested a bit.

193
00:13:19,577 --> 00:13:21,727
Soo Yeon,

194
00:13:21,727 --> 00:13:26,287
thinking about it, I've been too out of line.

195
00:13:26,287 --> 00:13:29,127
I'm sorry for causing trouble at home.

196
00:13:29,127 --> 00:13:31,207
I apologize.

197
00:13:31,827 --> 00:13:35,737
It happened because I'm old and easily worried.

198
00:13:35,737 --> 00:13:38,297
I hope you understand.

199
00:13:38,297 --> 00:13:41,010
I told Chairman Gong, too.

200
00:13:41,557 --> 00:13:44,307
I'll be careful from now on.

201
00:13:44,307 --> 00:13:46,207
Well...

202
00:13:47,757 --> 00:13:49,777
I'm home.

203
00:13:51,847 --> 00:13:54,087
Why are the lights off?

204
00:13:56,927 --> 00:13:59,087
Where's everyone?

205
00:13:59,087 --> 00:14:01,947
Mom. Dad.

206
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:04,857
Grandma!

207
00:14:06,287 --> 00:14:08,667
She's not here, either.

208
00:14:08,667 --> 00:14:11,707
Where did everyone go this late?

209
00:14:13,087 --> 00:14:15,407
Gosh, you're back, Pil Sung.

210
00:14:15,407 --> 00:14:17,227
I just got back.

211
00:14:17,227 --> 00:14:20,027
Where have you all been, by the way?

212
00:14:20,027 --> 00:14:23,257
Dad, why do you have a band-aid on your forehead?

213
00:14:23,257 --> 00:14:24,827
You have no idea.

214
00:14:24,827 --> 00:14:30,137
He was working as a day laborer at a construction site and he almost died.

215
00:14:30,137 --> 00:14:33,007
We're all coming back from the hospital right now.

216
00:14:33,007 --> 00:14:34,577
What did you say?

217
00:14:34,577 --> 00:14:38,087
Dad, you worked at a construction site?

218
00:14:38,087 --> 00:14:44,037
Ever since I got fired, I tried to earn money and

219
00:14:44,037 --> 00:14:48,370
start a business wearing a suit, but...

220
00:14:49,047 --> 00:14:51,330
I was wrong.

221
00:14:52,007 --> 00:14:55,947
Whether it's a warehouse or a construction site,

222
00:14:55,947 --> 00:14:58,837
I want to work with my own hands.

223
00:14:58,837 --> 00:15:02,417
So, no one should stop me. Not even you, Mom.

224
00:15:02,417 --> 00:15:06,137
I feel too guilty to not work anymore.

225
00:15:06,137 --> 00:15:08,457
I understand what you mean,

226
00:15:08,457 --> 00:15:11,877
but working at a warehouse or a construction site at your age is too much.

227
00:15:11,877 --> 00:15:15,647
Yes, Honey. Do something less demanding, at least.

228
00:15:15,647 --> 00:15:18,537
What if you get injured again?

229
00:15:18,537 --> 00:15:23,617
I thought I'd die from a heart attack when I heard from the hospital.

230
00:15:23,617 --> 00:15:27,417
So, look for a different job while resting, okay?

231
00:15:27,417 --> 00:15:30,717
No easy and cushy job would wait for me.

232
00:15:30,717 --> 00:15:34,387
I should be glad I even got this work in this economy.

233
00:15:34,387 --> 00:15:37,187
And I got injured because I wasn't good at my job

234
00:15:37,187 --> 00:15:39,967
and had no skills. It was a mistake.

235
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:45,217
This won't happen from now on. So please stop, everyone.

236
00:15:45,217 --> 00:15:47,217
Aigoo, goodness gracious.

237
00:15:47,217 --> 00:15:52,157
This happened because you've been complaining about money to him.

238
00:15:52,157 --> 00:15:55,807
You nag at him just because you have this house, but—

239
00:15:55,807 --> 00:15:58,587
Mom, that's not right.

240
00:15:58,587 --> 00:16:01,107
Why do you keep blaming her?

241
00:16:01,107 --> 00:16:04,027
Don't you know why I'm doing this?

242
00:16:09,347 --> 00:16:12,187
Anyway, don't say anything to me from now on.

243
00:16:12,187 --> 00:16:15,577
I'll manage my business myself.

244
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:38,827
 Oppa! 

245
00:16:38,827 --> 00:16:40,347
 Do Ra. 

246
00:16:40,347 --> 00:16:42,057
 Oppa... 

247
00:16:42,057 --> 00:16:46,577
 Gosh, you acted tough, but you were a scaredy-cat. 

248
00:16:48,617 --> 00:16:51,777
Why do I keep thinking about Pil Sung?

249
00:16:51,777 --> 00:16:54,107
Why on earth?

250
00:16:55,977 --> 00:16:57,847
By chance...

251
00:16:59,577 --> 00:17:04,517
No, no, no... What are you thinking, Park Do Ra?

252
00:17:04,517 --> 00:17:08,187
Yes, he was my first love, no matter what.

253
00:17:08,187 --> 00:17:12,717
I got confused since I haven't seen him for 15 years. That's right.

254
00:17:12,717 --> 00:17:16,657
Park Do Ra, you can't do this to someone you work with.

255
00:17:16,657 --> 00:17:18,987
Get it together, Park Do Ra.

256
00:17:21,477 --> 00:17:24,017
Get it together, seriously.

257
00:17:31,617 --> 00:17:34,057
By the way, I wonder what he's up to?

258
00:17:44,637 --> 00:17:47,457
   

259
00:17:52,347 --> 00:17:54,407
What?

260
00:17:54,967 --> 00:17:57,737
Gosh, why is he so cute?

