710
00:45:52,055 --> 00:45:55,265
- Really? Let me do it. 
 - No, your hands are dirty.

711
00:46:09,495 --> 00:46:11,695
Director!

712
00:46:14,885 --> 00:46:17,615
Assistant Director Go...

713
00:46:17,615 --> 00:46:18,935
Yes, me?

714
00:46:18,935 --> 00:46:21,615
I need to talk to you about something.

715
00:46:21,615 --> 00:46:24,085
Could we chat for a second?

716
00:46:25,145 --> 00:46:27,905
Oh, okay. Thank you.

717
00:46:32,195 --> 00:46:34,715
What's going on? Is something wrong?

718
00:46:35,495 --> 00:46:37,685
The thing is...

719
00:46:37,685 --> 00:46:39,915
You know...

720
00:46:41,195 --> 00:46:45,615
I couldn't sleep a wink because I kept thinking about the tteokbokki from last time.

721
00:46:45,615 --> 00:46:48,565
So, could you take me there again today?

722
00:46:48,565 --> 00:46:51,895
As you know, I can't just go alone.

723
00:46:53,965 --> 00:46:56,815
Did you scream at the top of your lungs to tell me that?

724
00:46:56,815 --> 00:46:59,875
Gosh, was I that loud?

725
00:46:59,875 --> 00:47:03,815
Yes, you screamed. I thought something happened.

726
00:47:03,815 --> 00:47:05,217
I'm sorry.

727
00:47:05,895 --> 00:47:09,345
I must've been loud because I was wearing headphones.

728
00:47:09,345 --> 00:47:12,795
Anyway, you're going with me because the shoot ends early today, okay?

729
00:47:12,795 --> 00:47:14,465
Okay.

730
00:47:19,225 --> 00:47:22,605
Park Do Ra, why did you suddenly mention tteokbokki?

731
00:47:22,605 --> 00:47:25,135
Why do I care if Sook Ja puts an ointment or a band-aid on him?

732
00:47:25,135 --> 00:47:26,975
What does that have to do with me?

733
00:47:26,975 --> 00:47:32,095
Why did I yell his name so loudly?

734
00:47:35,715 --> 00:47:39,545
Okay. Just eat tteokbokki...

735
00:47:39,545 --> 00:47:42,417
and get over your feelings from the deserted island

736
00:47:43,025 --> 00:47:47,935
and the 12-year-old Park Do Ra's feelings... completely.

737
00:47:47,935 --> 00:47:50,905
Chairman, you're having lunch with Chairman Kim at 12.

738
00:47:50,905 --> 00:47:52,565
Oh, okay.

739
00:47:55,835 --> 00:47:58,465
- Let me help you! 
 - You go ahead.

740
00:47:59,135 --> 00:48:00,845
Pil Sung.

741
00:48:00,845 --> 00:48:04,575
Oh, hello, Chairman.

742
00:48:04,575 --> 00:48:07,955
I heard there will be a shoot here today.

743
00:48:07,955 --> 00:48:09,565
I didn't know it was yours.

744
00:48:09,565 --> 00:48:12,035
Yes. We're done, so we're putting things away now.

745
00:48:12,035 --> 00:48:13,685
Is that so?

746
00:48:13,685 --> 00:48:16,375
Why don't we have some tea since you're here?

747
00:48:16,375 --> 00:48:18,285
Are you available?

748
00:48:18,875 --> 00:48:20,485
Yes, that should work.

749
00:48:20,485 --> 00:48:25,895
You were in high school when your grandfather passed, right?

750
00:48:25,895 --> 00:48:30,965
Yes, I was grateful that you came to the funeral.

751
00:48:32,195 --> 00:48:37,905
You were a kid then and grew up to be a nice young man.

752
00:48:37,905 --> 00:48:40,885
That's why I was so surprised the last time I saw you.

753
00:48:40,885 --> 00:48:42,825
I only knew because my wife told me.

754
00:48:42,825 --> 00:48:45,295
I didn't recognize you at all at first.

755
00:48:45,295 --> 00:48:49,325
- I did grow a lot, didn't I? 
 - Yes, you did.

756
00:48:49,325 --> 00:48:52,495
How did you grow so tall?

757
00:48:52,495 --> 00:48:55,115
My mom actually cooked meat for me every day.

758
00:48:55,115 --> 00:48:58,585
She said I need to eat well to be healthy, and I need to be healthy to study hard.

759
00:48:58,585 --> 00:49:01,545
So I had meat, fruit, and milk every day.

760
00:49:01,545 --> 00:49:05,005
And at some point, the ground seemed to be getting further away.

761
00:49:05,005 --> 00:49:08,055
What? The ground seemed further away?

762
00:49:08,055 --> 00:49:11,715
So I told my mom, "Mom, the ground looks so far away!"

763
00:49:11,715 --> 00:49:14,035
And she laughed a lot.

764
00:49:14,035 --> 00:49:16,965
Gosh, you're so funny.

765
00:49:17,705 --> 00:49:19,485
Drink.

766
00:49:27,705 --> 00:49:31,355
I could run into her anytime, anywhere. Will I avoid her every time?

767
00:49:31,355 --> 00:49:34,505
No, I should straighten things out...

768
00:49:34,505 --> 00:49:36,835
and take care of things the right way.

769
00:49:38,945 --> 00:49:43,135
Yes, and no woman would say no to a designer purse.

770
00:49:45,015 --> 00:49:48,285
Life gets difficult once a woman gets resentful.

771
00:49:53,935 --> 00:49:57,425
- Welcome. 
 - Welcome.

